The paper deals with computational geometry problems involving probability distributions, which is a topic that falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of probability distributions also suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses data structures and algorithms for approximating distributions, which could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
